  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Where can I find a power outlet for my laptop at Melbourne Airport?",
  "response": "As of my knowledge cutoff in October 2023, Melbourne Airport (also known as Tullamarine Airport) offers several locations where you can access power outlets to charge your laptop and other electronic devices. Here's a guide to help you find suitable spots:\n\n### **1. **Departure and Arrival Areas\n- **Seating Zones:** Many seating areas throughout the terminals are equipped with power outlets. Look for tables with built-in electrical sockets or designated charging spots.\n- **Gate Areas:** Near boarding gates, especially in international and premium lounges, you\u2019ll often find accessible power sources.\n\n### **2. **Airport Lounges\n- **Airline Lounges:** If you have access to airline lounges (such as Qantas Lounge, Virgin Lounge, or other partner lounges), these typically provide ample power outlets, comfortable seating, and a quiet environment for working or charging devices.\n- **Pay-Per-Use Lounges:** Some lounges offer paid access regardless of your airline or ticket class, providing facilities including power outlets.\n\n### **3. **Business and Work Stations\n- **Dedicated Work Areas:** Certain sections of the terminal are designated as business areas, featuring workstations with power access.\n- **Co-Working Spaces:** Some airports have incorporated co-working spaces where travelers can work and charge their devices; check if Melbourne Airport offers this service.\n\n### **4. **Cafes and Restaurants\n- **Dining Establishments:** Many cafes and restaurants within the airport provide power outlets for customers. While there's no guarantee, it's often acceptable to ask for permission to use an outlet while enjoying a purchase.\n\n### **5. **Charging Stations\n- **Public Charging Points:** Look out for dedicated charging stations scattered throughout the terminals. These may include USB ports and standard electrical outlets.\n- **Information Desks:** Some information kiosks or help points may offer charging solutions or direct you to the nearest outlet.\n\n### **6. **Wi-Fi Areas\n- **Connected Zones:** Areas with free Wi-Fi access often have available power outlets, making them convenient spots to charge your laptop while staying connected.\n\n### **Tips to Locate Power Outlets:**\n- **Airport Maps:** Visit the [Melbourne Airport Official Website](https://www.melbourneairport.com.au/) to access detailed terminal maps highlighting amenities, including power outlet locations.\n- **Mobile Apps:** Use the Melbourne Airport app if available, which may offer real-time information and interactive maps to help locate charging points.\n- **Ask Airport Staff:** Don\u2019t hesitate to inquire with airport personnel or at information desks\u2014they can provide directions to the nearest power sources.\n- **Signage:** Keep an eye out for signs indicating \"Power Outlets,\" \"Charging Stations,\" or \"Wi-Fi Zones,\" which usually mark areas where you can charge your devices.\n\n### **Additional Considerations:**\n- **Extension Cords:** If access is limited, you might consider bringing a compact extension cord or a portable power strip to increase your flexibility in finding outlets.\n- **Battery Packs:** Carrying a fully charged portable power bank can be a good backup in case you\u2019re unable to find a nearby power source when needed.\n\n### **Final Note:**\nFacilities and their availability can change, so it\u2019s a good idea to verify the latest information before your trip by checking Melbourne Airport\u2019s official website or contacting their customer service. This will ensure you have the most accurate and up-to-date details regarding power outlet locations and other amenities.\n\nSafe travels and happy charging!",
